# BIM Structural Annotation — BlenderBIM / IFC

Semantic labelling of structural BIM models for AI digital twin development.

## Overview
This repository documents structural model annotation work using BlenderBIM/Bonsai and FreeCAD BIM/IFC. Models are labelled at the element level — beams, columns, slabs, and walls — following IFC standards for interoperability.

## Tools Used
- BlenderBIM / Bonsai
- FreeCAD BIM / IFC workbench
- IFC 4.x schema

## Annotation Schema
| Label | IFC Class | Description |
|-------|-----------|-------------|
| `BEAM_Lx` | IfcBeam | Horizontal structural beams |
| `COL_x` | IfcColumn | Vertical columns |
| `SLAB_GF` | IfcSlab | Floor and roof slabs |
| `WALL_xx` | IfcWall | Load-bearing wall elements |

## Sample Output
```
Building_Model_v1.ifc
├── COL_A    → IfcColumn [labelled]
├── COL_B    → IfcColumn [labelled]
├── BEAM_L1  → IfcBeam   [labelled]
└── SLAB_GF  → IfcSlab   [labelled]
```

